914	   Figure 3. PRO model simulations of impaired motivation. In all plots, the y-axis shows the 915	   probability of engaging in the task (left panel) and the model activity (right panel). The x-axis 916	   shows four possible effort levels, parametrically increasing from easy (level 1) to hard (level 4). 917	   Grey lines indicate low reward upon task completion. Black lines indicate high reward upon 918	   task completion. a. Simulation 1. Behavioral and neural predictions for healthy controls. The 919	   table on the right illustrates the hypotheses of possible impairments as modeled with the PRO 920	   model, and relative explanation. We hypothesize two core possible mechanisms driving 921	   impairments in patients. The first is altered global salience, with either an overall increased 922	   effort salience (simulation 2), or an overall increased reward salience (simulation 3). The 923	   second is mismatch between predicted and actual outcome, with either a possible

	  

39	  

bioRxiv preprint doi: https://doi.org/10.1101/171637; this version posted August 2, 2017. The copyright holder for this preprint (which was not certified by peer review) is the author/funder, who has granted bioRxiv a license to display the preprint in perpetuity. It is made available under aCC-BY-NC-ND 4.0 International license.
924	   overestimation of predicted effort (as compared to actual, simulation 4) or a possible 925	   underestimation of the predicted reward (as opposed to actual, simulation 5). b-e. Simulations 926	   2 through 5. Behavioral (choices) and neural (model activity) predictions under the different 927	   hypotheses.
